Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo A leader of the Osun State chapter of the New Nigeria Peoples Party, Mr. Tosin Odeyemi, has urged the All Progressives Congress to prevail on its leaders and members not to disrupt the peace in the state. Odeyemi gave the warning in a statement, in Osogbo, on Monday, asking APC to resolve the rift between Governor Gboyega Oyetola and his predecessor, Rauf Aregbesola. YOU MAY ALSO LIKE: Three arraigned for invading palace, beating up Osun monarch He warned the APC not to allow its internal crisis to lead to the breakdown of law and order in the state. The statement read, “It is unfortunate that while the teeming populace of the state is still battling economic crisis due to COVID-19, the ruling party is towing the path of violence as it allows its factional crisis to snowball into public warfare. READ ALSO: Governors’ intervention will help resolve Imo crisis, says APC “It is also unfortunate that the former Governor and now Minister of Interior, Ogbeni Rauf Aregbesola, can allow sentiments to take over him to make statements capable of heating up the polity unnecessarily. “Our people have enough to battle already than for the ruling party to unleash another political crisis on the masses. A word is enough for the wise!”